Author: Jheddi
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: The Blockscart Marketplace will accept multiple types of cryptocurrencies as payment options. However, there are so many different cryptocurrencies in existence, that this would likely require a way for customers to alternate between currencies if necessary.  Blockscart is also looking into the potential option of developing something called BLOCPAY, which is similar to Bitpay, only for Blockscart. This essentially has the opportunity to provide an easier conversion to fiat funds for involved parties.  really great project. im looking forward to it.

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: I'm not sure where you quoted us converting funds into fiat. We will not be offering this.  Also, we will not be offering multiple cryptocurrencies, we will offer a select few that will benefit us and vendors.  If a ethereum based company can offer us something like exchange listing, we will offer their token as a payment option.  Until that happens it will be only Ethereum and BLOC.  Tim - CEO Blockscart

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: Thank you all for your support.  A message from our CEO:  üîäBlockscart is ready to launch  Hey everyone, I wanted to let you know that our developers have completed the Blockscart marketplace and we will be looking to launch within the next 28 days.  We will not enable to payment gateway until we believe that there are enough vendors on the platform to allow a good flow of trade.  Within the next 7 days, documents will be attached to our website with instructions on how to sell or buy on the marketplace.  To start off payments, we will be initially allowing for payments to be offered in Ethereum. This will allow us to build BLOC on exchanges to create value and then convert it so BLOC becomes the payment method. We will not remove Ethereum until we believe BLOC can sustain on its own and offer vendors a great value to accept.  As a buyer, all you will need to do is connect your desktop to Metamask or an ethereum based Dapp. Brave, Cipher browser or Metamask.  To get the marketplace out there in the timeframe, we will be launching the desktop browser version and then we will complete the mobile browser funtioning and mobile app in due course.  Our goals are to get as many vendors and sellers on board as quickly as possible.  If you have any questions then please ask our team.  If you wish to sell on the Blockscart Marketplace then we will place a google document form with contact details so we can start the boarding process.   Blockscarts aim is to be the world's first and free ecommerce marketplace for buyers and sellers in the cryptocurrency world.  Thank you all for your support.  Tim - CEO Blockscart.

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: It wont be easy to convert everyone over to a cryptocurrency only fee free marketplace but we believe that with the growing media around this technology, starting off with a simple marketplace linked up to blockchain and p2p payments through the main net will allow for a new wave of e-commerce platforms.  The team believes that if we can start this off then others will follow suite and what we mean by this is that all other ecommerce marketplaces will have no choice but to eventually offer free listings.  What happens if Blockscart complete this mission?  fee free marketplaces everywhere.  Next steps are to look to offer a similar platform by using the origin protocol allowing for smart contracts and sales of high value assets like property and deeded ownerships.

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: There has been a lot of interest from developers looking to join the team but that will be step 2. Get a fee free marketplace out there and then develop it further.  Baby steps. no running before walking as they say.  We found that platforms like open bazaar and bitify where essentially darknet marketplaces which have no control or care for whats sold.  The inevitable truth is that cyptocurrency will soon be regulated worldwide. By offering this type marketplace now, will put us in a position to further develop into a global brand.

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: Yes we believe so, that initial adoption will be slow, but since more and more people are getting into crypto day by day even in this bear market. IT is the sign that people want the change and freedom to do and control things in their own way. About the strategy part, initially we will tie up will big players and simultaneously we will promote it to the general public to open an store.  More people are joining us on blockscart and word of mouth is the best way forward as of now. But, in future we will use every marketing channel as possible to get this out there.  Feel free to PM me or email me at akhil.g@blockscart.co.uk for more queries.

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: Thanks for your questions Notin2.  We believe we underestimated the price of BLOC. We offered it at a low rate at start to see what benefits it could bring. Originally it was set as a discount token but we changed it to make it a payment token.  Once it is listed on an exchange with value then we can change the marketplace so only BLOC is the payment option.  With 18 decimal places.  We can allow for other tokens or coins to be used at our discretion. As long as they are Ethereum based.  Starting with ETH as payment option then add BLOC when on trading exchange.  ETH can be converted to FIAT quickly so vendors have no issues with it.  All prices are converted from dollar to eth with a live exchange feed. This means prices cannot inflate or deflate based on the market as its set against the Dollar.  If a product is $400 and Eth is worth that then it will be 1 eth. if it changes then the payment gateway will also change to represent the dollar value to ETH.

Author: Blockscart
Title: [ANN][COMPLETE] BLOCKSCART OLD THREAD.
Body: Right now, if you were to sell on any e-commerce platform, Amazon, ebay, Etsy etc, they charge to do so. Not only this but they learn your sales data which they use to sell the products themselves at a lower rate as per bulk buy.  We are fresh, we are different. We offer fee free trade with free payment gateway options (gas only cost).  As long as the products are legal, they can be sold.  We are creating the first stage of e-commerce on the blockchain and again, there are no costs.  Want to set up a business? We can help you do that with zero costs.  OUR COMPETITORS: Open Bazzar, Bitify, Storiqa (when they have a working platform) are more likely to go Silkroad style platforms due to them not having any ability to manage what products can be sold.  We on the other hand have created what is called a Hybrid marketplace that coexists with central and decentral style marketplaces allowing for early infrastructure to develop then to completely integrate everything into the Ethereum network.  We are also looking at other Blockchains to move over to in the future, if we can.

If they accept our BLOC token then they will be opening up areas for BLOC holders to spend elsewhere.
